# Personal baselines and voice profiles. These are voice-cloning inputs.
# The recommended layout keeps them in a sibling directory outside this repo;
# the patterns below are defensive in case any private corpus lands here.
*_voice_profile.md
*_voice_profile.json
*PRIVATE*
*private*
# Exception (R5 contract fixtures): the producer-owned golden envelopes under
# references/contract_fixtures/ are normalized, sentinelized, dependency-free
# CONTRACT fixtures — not real voice-clone artifacts. pov_voice_profile.json
# matches the *_voice_profile.json privacy glob above, so re-include the
# fixtures explicitly; the ratchet still covers every other path. (The
# generator + drift gate guarantee these carry only <fixture> sentinels and
# representative values, never a real corpus.)
!plugins/setec-voiceprint/references/contract_fixtures/*.json

# Claude Code agent harness state. The .claude/worktrees/ directory holds
# temporary git worktrees the agent harness manages during sub-agent runs;
# it's harness-managed state, not project content.
.claude/

# Internal working directory: working roadmap, session logs, design notes,
# review correspondence, commit-slice plans, and other artifacts that inform
# the project's evolution but are not part of the public release.
internal/

# Audit-output staging. Audit outputs against specific manuscripts should
# live outside this repo entirely (in the private workspace next to the
# manuscript itself), not be ignored *here* by name. This pattern is a
# fallback for stray output files that haven't been relocated yet, but
# the policy is: real audit outputs do not belong in this repo, ignored
# or otherwise. Naming specific titles in a tracked file (even via .gitignore)
# would itself disclose what the framework is meant to keep private.
audits-private/
output/
runs/
gi_runs/

# Plugin or vendoring staging directories should live outside this repo;
# this pattern is a fallback for stray files that haven't been relocated.
*-integration/

# Python
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.coverage
htmlcov/
build/
dist/

# Virtual environments
.venv/
venv/
env/

# Editor/OS artifacts
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Local environment files
.env
.env.local

# References-side working drafts. The references/ directory ships public
# spec docs; references/_drafts/ holds work-in-progress that hasn't been
# committed yet (e.g., downstream-integration handoff specs awaiting
# consumer-side decisions). Files here are discoverable on disk but not
# tracked.
plugins/setec-voiceprint/references/_drafts/
